3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Phemex calculates TON/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average premium between perpetual and spot prices. The exchange caps funding rates at ±0.75% per cycle to prevent extreme payments. Positions held at funding time automatically pay or receive the funding amount based on long/short direction and rate polarity."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TON","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON's integration with Telegram's ecosystem creates unique trading patterns with funding rate opportunities during ecosystem updates and user adoption surges. The token's large trading volume ensures sufficient liquidity for arbitrage positions, while its Layer 1 status generates sustained trading interest from DeFi participants."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON/USDT on Phemex has exhibited funding rate spikes above 0.3% during major ecosystem announcements and integration launches. The pair typically maintains slightly positive funding rates due to structural long bias from Telegram ecosystem participants. During bear market periods, funding rates can turn negative as institutional traders short against spot holdings. Weekend periods often show reduced funding volatility due to lower Asian trading hours activity."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Strategy Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Optimal TON arbitrage involves monitoring funding rates above 0.2% while maintaining spot TON holdings on exchanges with efficient withdrawal systems. Phemex's 0.01% maker fees significantly reduce strategy costs compared to higher-fee exchanges. Cross-exchange arbitrage works best when combining Phemex shorts with spot longs on major exchanges like Binance or OKX. Position sizing should account for TON's moderate volatility and potential slippage during high-activity periods."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON's price correlation with broader Layer 1 tokens requires hedging against sector-wide movements that could overwhelm funding rate gains. Phemex's smaller user base occasionally creates liquidity gaps during rapid price movements, requiring careful position entry timing. Telegram-related news events can cause rapid funding rate changes that may reverse arbitrage positions. Smart money typically exits funding rate trades 2-3 hours before funding time to avoid last-minute rate manipulation."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical TON/USDT funding rates on Phemex?","answer":"TON/USDT funding rates on Phemex typically range from -0.1% to 0.4% per 8-hour cycle, with higher rates during ecosystem milestones. The average funding rate over 30-day periods usually stays between 0.05% to 0.15% due to moderate long bias."},{"question":"How do Phemex's low fees impact TON arbitrage profitability?","answer":"Phemex's 0.01% maker fees significantly improve TON arbitrage returns compared to exchanges charging 0.02-0.04%. This fee advantage can increase net profits by 15-25% on frequent trading strategies. Combined with 8-hour funding cycles, the fee structure enables profitable arbitrage at lower funding rate thresholds."},{"question":"What TON-specific risks should arbitrageurs consider?","answer":"TON's connection to Telegram creates event-driven volatility that can quickly change funding dynamics and overwhelm rate-based profits. The token's relative youth means less predictable funding patterns compared to established assets. Regulatory developments affecting Telegram could impact TON trading volumes and liquidity."},{"question":"When do TON funding rates typically peak on Phemex?","answer":"TON funding rates often peak during Asian trading hours (00:00-08:00 UTC funding cycle) when Telegram ecosystem activity is highest. Major peaks occur around ecosystem announcements, new feature launches, or significant partnership reveals. Weekend rates tend to be more subdued due to reduced institutional participation."}]}]
